      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SHES CRYSTAL NZ (8) is a newcomer to the Jack Butler yard from NZ. Last raced when successful by 2.7 metres at Rangiora four months ago and has been readied for this with two nice trials here. Can travel in a nice spot from this draw and the sprint lane is in play. Could kick off in Queensland with a win. MISS BAY KING COLE (4) worked to the front and proved too good last time out by 1.7 metres in a strong performance at this circuit and distance. She finds another suitable assignment so could back that up. TWO TICKS NZ (2) has been racing well at Redcliffe and a good draw could see her competitive again. WARRAWEE FLYER (5) deserves respect having won the last two times she raced here.",
